<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-1824] Schema only fully propagates from seeds</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1824</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you have nodes X, Y, and Z, and Y already has some schema, but X and Z do not, and X is the seed node for the cluster, X will pick up the schema from Y, but it will never propagate to Z.  If X has the schema, it will propagate to both Y and Z.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12492268">CASSANDRA-1824</key>
            <summary>Schema only fully propagates from seeds</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21133&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
